repo.name: cython

body:
This should provide a version independent way of identifying a Cython function (at least going forwards) - all future versions of versions of Cython will match the same abstract base.

In principle it could be extended to other shared types if useful (e.g. generator, coroutine).

(This does periodically come up as a request, although I can't find an existing issue. I think this is a better alternative to https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6754 at least)

comment_data.body: I need to have another look at this actually. I don't think GetAttr works well with critical sections so I may need to make it more robust or not bother

This seems an unusual name for an ABC class. Why not `"CythonFunction"`?
```suggestion
    __Pyx_RegisterCommonTypeWithAbc((PyObject*)mstate->__pyx_CyFunctionType, "CythonFunction");
```

I don't see why we should have different ABC classes for different Cython versions. Why not just look up `abc.CythonFunction` directly, and only if that fails. add it? The low-level, version specific details of a CyFunction shouldn't really matter to Python-level users. And the Python interface is really just "this is a function, implemented with (some) Cython".

That's definitely what I intended to do and I think that's what I've done.

I put it in the `cython_runtime` module on the basis that it's our module, but is version independent. Similarly the name of class is also version independent. 

It sounds like you'd prefer it added to the `abc` module instead, which also seems reasonable. 

But yes - the aim is definitely a single ABC covering functions from all (future) Cython versions.

commit.message:
Add a CyFunction abstract base class

This should provide a version independent way of identifying a
Cython function (at least going forwards) - all future versions of
versions of Cython will match the same abstract base.

In principle it could be extended to other shared types if useful
(e.g. generator, coroutine).
Move definitions to collections.abc; change name
Disable part of test where limited API is unlikely to work

title: Add a CyFunction abstract base class
